    <text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
      <body>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <p xml:id="Aink416-kilavi">paruvam kuṟittup pirinta talaimakaṉ paruvattiṟku muṉṉē vantu talaiviyoṭu kūṭic cellāniṉṟuḻi ataṟku iṉiyaṉāyt taṉṉuḷḷē colluvāṉ pōṉṟu talaivi aṟiyumāṟṟāl kūṟiyatu.</p>
          <p xml:lang="en">The hero, who had separated after indicating the season [of his return], haveing returned before the season and having united with the heroine, when going, being sweet about that and speaking to himself, in a way in which the heorine would know [it], declared [this].</p>
        </div>
        <div rend="parallel">
          <lg xml:id="Aink416">
            <l>pōtār naṟuntukaḷ kaviṉip puṟaviṟ</l>
                <l>ṟātārntu</l>
                <l>kaḷiccurum paraṟṟuṅ kāmar putaliṉ</l>
                <l>maṭappiṭi taḻīiya māvē</l>
                <l>cuṭarttoṭi maṭavaraṟ puṇarntaṉam yāmē.</l>
          </lg>
          <lg xml:lang="en">
            <l>Around the desirable bushes where,</l>
            <l>having becoming beautiful because of the fragrant pollen-dust</l>
            <l>that had grown full in the flowers in the woodlands,</l>
            <l>and having become full of nectar, intoxicated bees hum,</l>
            <l>the bull-elephant embraced the naive female.</l>
            <l>I united with the naive women with glowing bangles.</l>
          </lg>
        </div>
      </body>
    </text>
    
